<span id="freeTextContainer9643281988644255538">Read many years ago, this is one of the top three books by Pamuk which I love the most. The other two being <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2517.My_Name_Is_Red' title='My Name Is Red by Orhan Pamuk' rel='nofollow noopener'>My Name Is Red</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11691.Snow' title='Snow by Orhan Pamuk' rel='nofollow noopener'>Snow</a> - obvious choices.<br/><br/>No one makes old and modern Turkey come alive on page like Pamuk.<br/><br/>A re-read is on the horizon. </span>
  <span id="freeText9643281988644255538" style="display:none">Read many years ago, this is one of the top three books by Pamuk which I love the most. The other two being <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2517.My_Name_Is_Red" title="My Name Is Red by Orhan Pamuk" rel="nofollow noopener">My Name Is Red</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11691.Snow" title="Snow by Orhan Pamuk" rel="nofollow noopener">Snow</a> - obvious choices.<br /><br />No one makes old and modern Turkey come alive on page like Pamuk.<br /><br />A re-read is on the horizon. </span>
